action_plan.description: Load the dataset to explore the available data and identify potential phenomena worth researching.
Perform exploratory data analysis to identify patterns, correlations, or anomalies in the dataset.
Generate visualizations to better understand the relationships between different variables.
Formulate a hypothesis based on the observed patterns or correlations in the data.
Validate the hypothesis using statistical tests and report the findings.

decisions_and_justifications.decision: Perform exploratory data analysis to identify potential research phenomena.
decisions_and_justifications.justification: Exploratory data analysis helps in uncovering hidden patterns, correlations, and anomalies that can lead to the formulation of a research hypothesis.

summary: The dataset will be analyzed to identify potential phenomena worth researching. Exploratory data analysis will be conducted to uncover patterns or correlations that can lead to a hypothesis.
next_steps: Conduct exploratory data analysis to identify patterns or correlations.
Generate visualizations to better understand the relationships between variables.
Formulate and validate a hypothesis based on the findings.
conclusion: A hypothesis will be generated based on the exploratory analysis of the dataset, focusing on patterns or correlations that are statistically significant.
